commText: Rahane and Ravindra are at the crease. Rahane is on strike. Umesh Yadav will open the attack
Umesh Yadav to Rahane, no run, outswinger outside off stump, Jinks shoulders arms as he wants a sighter
If the ball comes on nicely, this is the kind of opportunity Jinks will be eager for. Can he maximzie?
Umesh Yadav to Rahane, 1 run, controlled steer down to third man
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, no run, plays the cover drive but picks out the fielder
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, 1 run, pushed to mid-off and he's off the mark
Umesh Yadav to Rahane, no run, outswinger finishing just outside off stump, Rahane knocks it to the on-side
Direct-hit from Miller. Rachin is gone!
Umesh Yadav to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Umesh Yadav to Rahane, out Ravindra Run Out!! What a gift of a wicket from CSK. Stunning piece of fielding from Miller that made this possible though. Rahane only looking to dab this. Looked his partner for a run and Rachin responded. Miller swooped in on the ball from backward point and underarmed the ball with a direct-hit. He had a great chance on a good pitch to return to form but it's a misjudgement that's cost him bad. Ravindra run out (Miller) 1(2)
Ruturaj Gaikwad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Sandeep Warrier, Right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Warrier to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Warrier to Rahane, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! In the airrrr, great catch from Tewatia stretching to the left. GT have bought both early wickets thanks to great fielding. Short of a length delivery, Rahane looks to work it to the on-side, seems like it bounced on him extra, did move away too, leading edge goes to the left of mid-off. Tewatia had to move to the left and he grabs it two-handed. CSK are rocked early. 2/2 in a crunch match. Rahane c Rahul Tewatia b Warrier 1(5)
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Warrier to Mitchell, no run, short delivery, Mitchell ducks under it
CSK opening partnership this IPL Inns: 12 Runs: 268 Avg: 22.33 RR: 7.73 50+: 2 - CSK's opening stand aggregate runs, average, RR and 50+ stands are the lowest among all teams this season.
Warrier to Mitchell, no run, fullish delivery, Mitchell drives firmly but finds mid-off
Warrier to Mitchell, 1 run, Mitchell wants to take it on, toe-ends this slap to mid-on
The onus is on the CSK captain again to save the side with the bat. Can he do it under pressure though?
Warrier to Gaikwad, no run, watchful defence to mid-wicket
Warrier to Gaikwad, no run, moves across the stumps before the bowler delivered. Defends this length delivery towards point
Ajinkya Rahane vs Pace this IPL Inns: 11 Runs: 164 Balls: 124 Dismissals: 8 Avg: 20.5 SR: 132.2
Umesh Yadav to Mitchell, 2 runs, short of length delivery, Mitchell slaps it square of the wicket for a couple
Umesh Yadav to Mitchell, no run, oh swing and bounce. Great diving take to the right in front of first slip by Wade. Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Mitchell looks to cut and misses
Umesh Yadav to Mitchell, FOUR, gives great intent on the slog, but Umesh Yadav got this to swing away, unfortunately for him the edge flies past slip and third man had no chance
Umesh Yadav to Mitchell, 1 run, swings too hard. Mitchell mistimes the pull to mid-on
Ruturaj is caught on the fence, Rashid claims the catch. Seems clean and Rutu already started walking. OUT
Umesh Yadav to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Umesh Yadav to Gaikwad, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! Is that the game there? Rashid was so calm under pressure and put on a massive smile with the tongue out that he didn't make a mess of it. Short delivery, Rutu pulls in the air, Rashid was at deep square leg and he took the catch inside the rope. Released it as he was going back and made sure his right leg wasn't touching the rope when he was taking the catch on the second attempt. Had to ensure he didn't overbalance and tough the cushion. This is a body blow for CSK and they seem down already. Third wicket for GT as well to great bit of fielding.Gaikwad c Rashid Khan b Umesh Yadav 0(3)
Moeen Ali, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Umesh Yadav to Moeen Ali, no run, edgeddd but doesn't carry to Wade. Fullish delivery outside off stump, Moeen looks to drive and gets an edge
Ruturaj Gaikwad vs Umesh Yadav in IPL Inns: 3 Runs: 17 Balls: 15 Dismissals: 2 Avg: 8.5 SR: 113.3
Warrier to Mitchell, 1 run, very full delivery, Mitchell drills it to mid-on
Warrier to Moeen Ali, no run, swing and a miss from Moeen as he gets beaten on the angle
Warrier to Moeen Ali, no run, beaten! Totally squared him up there. Full and outside off stump, Moeen looks to flick totally lost the line of the ball because it seamed off the pitch
Warrier to Moeen Ali, 1 run, short delivery, Moeen mistimes the pull to square leg
Warrier to Mitchell, SIX, finally a six from CSK. Full and in the slot, Mitchell waits and muscles this full delivery over long-on. He's been trying to tee off for a while and nails it now
Warrier to Mitchell, FOUR, full and on the leg stump, Mitchell lofts it over mid-on and gets four more. Mitchell is in the mood. Can he get quality company? Warrier punished for offering a slot ball
Umesh Yadav to Moeen Ali, FOUR, now Moeen slogs and manages to hit it wide of mid-on. Full delivery, Moeen closes the bat face as he swings, manages to middle it well enough
Umesh Yadav to Moeen Ali, 1 run, thick edge and it runs away to third man as Moeen swings too hard at this length delivery
Umesh Yadav to Mitchell, 1 run, short of length delivery, punched to point. Yes-no, direct-hit attempt at the striker's end missed and they get the run eventually with the overthrow

Umesh Yadav to Moeen Ali, FOUR, poor line! Short and down leg with no one behind square. Moeen gets inside the line and pulls it for four. Seems like Shubman isn't pleased with that bit of bowling from the bowler - not bowling to the field
Umesh Yadav to Moeen Ali, 1 run, short of a length delivery, Mo underedges it to mid-wicket
Umesh Yadav to Mitchell, no run, oh lovely short delivery. Mitchell was ready for the pull, had to bail out because it was pacy
Kartik Tyagi, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, wide, fired down leg
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, FOUR, edgeddd and four! Length delivery angling away, Moeen throws his bat at it and swings hard, thick edge flies over slip to the third man fence

Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, 2 runs, in the airrrr, mid-wicket runs back, Mohit makes a great attempt but it clears him. Really attacked for the catch. Short delivery that Moeen mistimed and got away with
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, wide, short delivery and too high
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, no run, good length delivery on the leg stump, Moeen works it to the on-side
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, good length delivery on the stumps, Moeen moves across to go leg-side but can only knocks it to mid-on
Kartik Tyagi to Mitchell, no run, short delivery, again Mitchell bails out of the pull and ducks
Kartik Tyagi to Mitchell, 1 run, full delivery, Mitchell looks to hit too hard and toe-ends it to long-on

Early timeout from GT. Brilliant powerplay for GT almost blowing the knockout punch on CSK for this game. The bowling has been pretty good but it's the fielding that's bought them all three wickets. All of them half-chances and all of them coverted. This is GT's game to lose. Their main weapons Noor and Rashid are yet to be used and the asking rate is 13.5 already.

Powerplay summary -- CSK top-order dismantled early -- Rachin is run out for 1 by Miller (0.6) -- Rahane dismissed for 1 by Warrier (1.1) -- Gaikwad holes out for a duck off Umesh (2.5) -- Mitchell, Moeen break the shackles with some good hits
Stat: This is the 2nd lowest powerplay total for CSK this season.
Sandeep Warrier [2.0-0-13-1] is back into the attack

Warrier to Mitchell, SIX, Mitchell swings across the line and just about clears deep square leg. Don't think he middled it, but the connection is good enough. Was fuller than a good length around off stump, in the slot for him and he went hard
Warrier to Mitchell, 1 run, short of length on off, pulled to deep midwicket
Warrier to Moeen Ali, no run, banged in short outside off, left alone. They've used the bouncer well so far, getting good height on it

Warrier to Moeen Ali, SIX, this one doesn't have good height on it, sits up around the chest for Moeen who nails the pull shot over midwicket for six. Was banged in at 140kph, but Moeen climbed all over it
Warrier to Moeen Ali, 1 run, good length ball slanting away outside off, Moeen drives loosely away from the body and it goes off a thick edge to deep third
Warrier to Mitchell, 1 run, 143.2kph good length ball outside off, Mitchell shuffles across and punches it to long-off
Still no spin. Rashid, Noor being held back
Kartik Tyagi to Mitchell, FOUR, short and wide, Mitchell goes after it and slaps it over backward point

Kartik Tyagi to Mitchell, FOUR, cracking shot down the ground! Good length ball on off, Mitchell clears the front leg and drives powerfully on the up. Loves playing in the V and absolutely hammers it past the umpire
Crowd buzzing now with chants of CSK

Kartik Tyagi to Mitchell, leg byes, 1 run, Mitchell misses out here! Close to 145kph, straying in line down leg and fine leg is in the ring. He looks to glance it fine but is late on it and gets hit on the thigh
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, no run, banged in short outside off, Moeen goes for the ramp but is beaten
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, back of a length on off, steered to backward point

Kartik Tyagi to Mitchell, FOUR, unlucky for the bowler! Mitchell had no clue against this short ball but still gets four. It climbs sharply on him, taking him by surprise as he leaves the bat hanging in hope more than anything else. But it flies off the edge over the keeper
Noor Ahmad, Left-arm wrist-spin, comes into the attack
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, 1 run, googly on middle and leg, length ball, Moeen tucks it behind square
Noor Ahmad to Mitchell, no run, 84.8kph, tossed up on off, googly, Mitchell gets on one knee and reverse-sweeps to backward point

Noor Ahmad to Mitchell, 2 runs, 92.7kph, full ball on leg stump, turning back in, Mitchell looks to loft down the ground but miscues it in the air off the inside half. It falls between long-on and deep midwicket
Noor Ahmad to Mitchell, 1 run, flat googly on off, back of a length, Mitchell opens the face and steers it to short third
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, no run, flat length ball outside off, turning away from Moeen who taps it gently to cover
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, 1 run, short and wide, Moeen cuts gently to backward point. He's not going hard because he's not picking him
Slip in place as Rashid comes on
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, leg byes, 1 run, appeal for LBW but this has clearly pitched outside leg. Flat length ball that turns in with a bit of zip, beating Moeen on the inside edge as he looks to clip it away

Rashid Khan to Mitchell, FOUR, googly on off, only slightly short but it's enough for Mitchell who rocks back and pulls hard wide of long-on. That's an excellent shot against someone like Rashid who's quick through the air and off the surface
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, driven to long-off for a single
Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, 1 run, length ball on off, googly, Moeen leans back and bunts it to long-on

Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, fifty for Mitchell who's found his rhythm in the last few matches after a quiet start to the tournament! Flat googly on leg, back of a length, cramps him up as he tucks it through square leg

Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, leg byes, 1 run, googly on leg stump, turns away off a length and hits the back leg as Moeen looks to defend. He scampers through for a single. Looks like there was some bat involved too
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, SIX, smashed over long-on! Excellent shot off a delivery that's not all that short. Length ball outside off, turning away, Moeen goes back and pulls hard down the ground
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, SIX, now this is shorter and it disappears for six more! Moeen slaps it hard straight back over the bowler's head
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, SIX, three in a row from Moeen! Noor goes for the googly but drops it short on middle, and Moeen unleashes another pull that goes sailing over backward square
GT are forced into a conference as Tewatia and Rashid go up to Noor for a chat
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, no run, flat length ball outside off, googly, Moeen blocks it from the crease
Noor Ahmad to Moeen Ali, 1 run, looks to fetch a ball from outside off for the slog-sweep, but drags it off the inside half through square leg
Noor Ahmad to Mitchell, 1 run, tossed up outside leg, googly, Mitchell gets down low and paddles it to short fine
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, FOUR, 97kph legbreak outside off, Mitchell dances down, gets close enough to the pitch and plays a lovely lofted drive over extra cover

Rashid Khan to Mitchell, SIX, boundaries flowing now. Full ball around off, close enough to the slot for Mitchell who clears the front leg and goes bang down the ground. Hardly much elevation but it still goes for six!
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, googly on middle and leg, length ball, Mitchell goes back and tucks it through midwicket
Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, no run, length ball on off, turning in, Moeen makes room and gently cutsto cover
Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, 1 run, length ball on leg stump, turning into the pads, Moeen goes back and pulls wide of long-on
This is the highest partnership for CSK this season.
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, full outside off, Mitchell swings hard looking to go down the ground but drags it off the inside half through midwicket. Was the googly from Rashid
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, no run, banged in short on off, Mitchell walks across the stumps to go for a premeditated scoop but is beaten
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, out Caught by Shahrukh Khan!! The slower ball from Mohit does the trick straightaway. 114kph length ball on off, Mitchell goes for a lofted shot down the ground but doesn't get hold of it. He miscues it in the air to the left of long-off, and Shahrukh takes a good running catch. Mohit hasn't had a great season, but he's broken this dangerous partnership immediately after coming on. Mitchell c Shahrukh Khan b Mohit Sharma 63(34) [4s-7 6s-3]
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, FOUR, almost a hattrick of golden ducks for Dube! Fuller than a length on off, on-pace delivery, and he is late on it as he goes for the drive. Front foot comes forward tentatively and he drags it off an inside edge past leg stump
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, no run, banged in short outside off, left alone
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length on off, slower one, and Dube dabs it gently into the off-side
Mohit Sharma to Moeen Ali, 1 run, 129.8kph length ball on off, Moeen gets forward and knocks it to long-off. The CSK players applaud as Moeen raises his half-century
Kartik Tyagi [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, Moeen backs away to the leg-side, looking to make room and Tyagi tries to follow him. It's a short of length delivery and Moeen cuts it to deep third
Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, banged in short, Dube goes for the pull, doesn't get hold of it but clears midwicket. Gets back for a couple of runs
Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length on off, Dube mistimes the pull through midwicket

Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, FOUR, 143kph, short of length delivery on off, Moeen hangs back and punches it sweetly through backward point. Oh he's timed it so well that it races away, giving the fielder in the deep no chance
Kartik Tyagi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, back of a length on off, Moeen punches to the left of backward point who cuts it off
There are three fielders in the deep on the leg-side for the short ball, none down the ground
Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, no run, sharp bouncer angling across off, Dube lets it go
Mohit Sharma to Moeen Ali, wide, slower bouncer that goes above Moeen's head and is called wide
Mohit Sharma to Moeen Ali, no run, slower full toss outside off at 108kph, dips late and Moeen is beaten on the drive. There was a hint of inswing too
Mohit Sharma to Moeen Ali, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohit Sharma to Moeen Ali, out Caught by Noor Ahmad!! Mohit has put GT in the driver's seat now in a matter of 8 balls. First the wicket of Mitchell, now Moeen. Noor almost makes a mess of it in the deep after getting into a bad position, but he recovers superbly. Back of a length on off, Moeen looks to slog but miscues it high in the air. Noor comes in more than he should have from the boundary, but is able to backpedal and take it with the reverse-cup. Moeen Ali c Noor Ahmad b Mohit Sharma 56(36) [4s-4 6s-4]
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, no run, short outside off, left alone
Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, no run, yorker outside off, Jadeja goes for a powerful drive but squeezes it off a thick inside edge onto pad
Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, FOUR, full outside off, Jadeja goes hard at it and smashes it down the ground, beating long-on to his left. Was struck powerfully, giving the fielder no chance

Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, FOUR, full and wide at 111kph, Jadeja reaches out and drills it through extra cover for four more. It was this very duel that decided the tournament last year, and Jadeja's winning the battle so far this time as well

Overs 7-15: - Warrier and Tyagi taken for 15 and 14 runs respectively - Noor bowls a momentum-killing 5-run over - Mitchell completes an excellent 27-ball fifty - Warrier and Tyagi taken for 15 and 14 runs respectively - Moeen takes Noor for hat-trick of sixes - Mitchell-Moeen record highest partnership of the season for CSK - Body blow from Mohit as he gets Mitchell for 63 - Dube struggles and Mohit delivers another punch by getting Moeen
Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, SIX, full ball on off stump, right in the slot for Dube who tonks it straight back for six. Just when you think the game is getting out of reach, CSK come roaring back

Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, FOUR, not well timed by Dube, but mid-off is in the ring and he clears the fielder comfortably. Short of length outside off and he slices it in the air going for the flat-batted smash. Enough bat on it for four

Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length on leg, Dube pulls in the air and Manohar charges in at deep backward square going for the catch. The ball falls well short of him and he does well to save the boundary by putting his body behind it
Kartik Tyagi to Jadeja, SIX, superbly scooped over short fine! 144.5kph full ball on middle, Jadeja bends his knees to get under it and uses the pace to his advantage
Kartik Tyagi to Jadeja, 1 run, back of a length delivery on leg, 143kph, cramps Jadeja for room and he taps it to the left of the bowler. A clean pick-up from Tyagi could've had Jadeja in trouble
Kartik Tyagi to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short and wide, slower one, makes Dube reach out for it and he slices it in the air over point. It falls well wide of sweeper cover and they settle for the single

Timeout! This match is not over yet with CSK needing 70 off four overs. Mohit is going to be key for GT. He's bowled two superb overs and the slower ball seems to be coming out well. Here he is again.
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 134kph good length ball outside off, Dube looks to slog but slices it in the air off the outside half. It falls well short of sweeper cover
Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, 1 run, slower bouncer on off, Jadeja goes for the pull but drags it off a thick under-edge to short fine

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, no run, Dube is asking Jadeja if he should go for a review for wide. No is the answer. Excellent short ball with good height on it, beats Dube on the pull and flies through to the keeper. Umpire says one bouncer for the over

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, wide, now umpire gives a wide, and GT have gone for the review. Slower ball wide of off, Dube looks to slog but fails to reach it. The ball is well outside the marker, and the decision is upheld
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Noor Ahmad!! Mohit strikes again and it's the big wicket of Dube! He's hanging around thinking there's a chance of a no-ball. But this full toss is clearly below the waist. Line is around off stump and he tries to slog, but miscues it in the air. Another catch for Noor at deep midwicket. Shivam Dube c Noor Ahmad b Mohit Sharma 21(13) [4s-2 6s-1]
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohit Sharma to Dhoni, 1 run, slower ball floated up on off, Dhoni gets forward and gently knocks it to long-off

Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, 2 runs, short of length on off, slower one, and Jadeja pulls it nicely through square leg. Takes a good tumbling stop in the deep from Umesh to cut it off. Another excellent over from Mohit who's making the task very difficult for CSK
Rashid Khan [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Rashid Khan to Dhoni, 1 run, flat length ball on middle and leg, Dhoni is happy to just go back and works it round the corner for a single
Rashid Khan to Jadeja, no run, flat outside off, Jadeja looks to cut but gets a thick edge to short third. Loud no from Dhoni for the single
Rashid Khan to Jadeja, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rashid Khan to Jadeja, out Caught by Miller!! Jadeja holes out in the deep and the game is all but done. Full ball on off, he looks to loft it down the ground but miscues it to long-on. Dolly for Miller. Jadeja c Miller b Rashid Khan 18(10) [4s-2 6s-1]
Mitchell Santner, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Rashid Khan to Santner, no run, flat length ball on middle, legbreak, and it almost goes right through Santner who's caught in the crease. He looks to punch it down the ground but gets an inside edge onto pad
Rashid Khan to Santner, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Rashid Khan to Santner, out Bowled!! He was saved by the inside edge first ball, but not this time. Flat length ball on middle and leg, Santner makes room to slog but it turns in past the inside edge and crashes into the top of leg. Santner b Rashid Khan 0(2)
Shardul Thakur, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rashid Khan to Thakur, 1 run, length ball on off, googly, Thakur gets forward and nudges it through the on-side
Mohit Sharma to Thakur, 1 run, slower bouncer at the head, Thakur mistimes the pull to deep backward square
Mohit Sharma to Dhoni, 1 run, length ball on off, Dhoni knocks it through midwicket

Mohit Sharma to Thakur, 1 run, slower bouncer outside off, Thakur looks to pull but is completely deceived by lack of pace. Somehow manages to slice it over the keeper's head. Short third chases it down

Mohit Sharma to Dhoni, SIX, one-handed six from Dhoni to give the sea of yellow something to cheer. Slower length ball outside off, seems to have deceived him for lack of pace as the bottom hand comes off while going for the slog. But he still manages to muscle it over midwicket
Mohit Sharma to Dhoni, 1 run, short of length delivery, slower one, Dhoni pulls to deep backward square

Mohit Sharma to Thakur, no run, back of a length outside off, slower one, Thakur hangs back and tries to hoist it over extra cover but is beaten. An excellent spell from Mohit comes to an end. Has sealed the deal in favour of GT
Rashid Khan to Dhoni, SIX, full around off, Dhoni shimmies down the pitch in a flash and whips it over deep midwicket

Rashid Khan to Dhoni, SIX, half-tracker at the stumps, and it disappears again! Another one-handed six from Dhoni as the bottom hand slips out of the handle. But he manages to pull it a long way back over square leg

Rashid Khan to Dhoni, no run, big appeal for LBW, not given! GT take the review. It's a googly on off, turns in off a length and goes past the inside edge in defence before hitting the back leg. Crowd waits with bated breath as though the match is on the line. Dhoni has a smile on his face. Is it too high? Yep, it's missing the stumps and the crowd roars
Now we have a spectator invading the field and falling at the feet of Dhoni. A bit of a delay as security takes the person away
Rashid Khan to Dhoni, no run, googly on off, Dhoni dances down and drills it on the bounce to long-on. Doesn't want to take the single
Rashid Khan to Dhoni, no run, googly down leg, Dhoni pulls to short fine

Rashid Khan to Dhoni, FOUR, another googly down the leg-side, and this time Dhoni pulls it to the long leg boundary. That's it. GT have kept their hopes alive in this tournament as they beat CSK by 35 runs

23:31 Local Time, 18:01 GMT, 23:31 IST: Fairly comfortable win for the hosts here in Ahmedabad in front of over 90000 people. Hundreds from Shubman Gill and Sai Sudharsan took them to 231 after being put into bat earlier in the evening. Should've probably got a few more in the final few overs, but it didn't matter in the end. CSK got off to a terrible start in the chase, losing three wickets in the first three overs. It took an excellent partnership between Mitchell and Moeen - CSK's highest of the season - to keep them in the hunt, but a cracking spell from Mohit Sharma sealed the deal for GT. This result keeps them alive, and also gives a boost to a few other teams in the race for the playoffs.

Ruturaj Gaikwad: Our fielding let us down, we gave away 10-15 runs extra I think, execution wise we were good, but they played some really good shots. You can't control batters when they are playing so well and going good. It's real quick, we got to fly next as we have a tough game in Chennai, so we got to turn up well there as well.

Rashid Khan: You love to watch those two (Gill and Sudharsan), really enjoyed the way they played, happy to be on the winning side though. Happy to get a couple of wickets, my body is feeling fetter. Had a back issue, it's good and it's better now, very soon I will be all fit. I have bowled against him (Dhoni), when he comes to play it's a different feeling, it gives us good energy, happy to play with him.
25 sixes is the 2nd most hit in an IPL match at Ahmedabad
Most sixes in an IPL season: 1124 in 2023 1063 in 2024* 1062 in 2022
Lowest team score before a 100+ 4th-wicket stand in IPL: 10 - CSK vs GT, Ahmedabad, 2024 20 - RCB vs SRH, Bengaluru, 2019 21 - KKR vs DC, Delhi, 2017

Gill, GT captain and POTM: Yeah just a cramp, nothing else (reason for being off the field). When you've got 100k people supporting you, becomes easier. Just the freeness of it. When we were batting out there, we didn't have any targets in mind. Were just maximising the opportunities in front of us. We have a good camaraderie between us. Even last year we batted a lot together. Lot of fun batting with him. In terms of numbers, definitely it is (best opening partnership for GT). Mohit bhai has done this for us the last couple of years. Even last year, his bowling was a revelation. Even this year, two three bad games can happen to anyone. At one point we thought 250 was there for the taking. In the last 2-3 overs they bowled well also. Just had a feeling we were 10-15 short - not in terms of the match but in terms of the NRR going forward.

As many as eight teams are still in the hunt for the playoffs as we go into the last two rounds of the league stages. For CSK, the road has become trickier as they now take on Rajasthan Royals before finishing against RCB who have won four in a row. Gujarat Titans, on the other hand, have no option but to win their remaining games while hoping for the best. That's it for now. Hope you enjoyed our coverage. This is Sagar Chawla signing off on behalf of Praveen Kumar, MS Ramakrishnan and Nikhil Jadhav. Goodbye!
